{"title_page": "Shame, Shame, Shame (Shirley & Company song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Shame, Shame, Shame\n| cover      = SandC Shame.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Shirley & Company]]\n| album      = Shame, Shame, Shame\n| B-side     = {{ubl|\"More Shame\" (U.K., Europe)|\"Shame, Shame, Shame\" (Instrumental) (U.S.)}}\n| released   = December 1974\n| format     = [[CD single]], [[Gramophone record|7\" single]], [[Gramophone record|12\" single]]\n| recorded   = 1974\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Disco]], [[Soul music|soul]]\n| length     = 3:47\n| label      = Vibration\n| writer     = [[Sylvia Robinson]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Cry, Cry, Cry, (Shirley & Company song)|Cry, Cry, Cry]],\n| next_year  = 1975\n}}\n\n\"'''Shame, Shame, Shame'''\" is a 1974 hit song written by [[Sylvia Robinson]], performed by American [[disco]] band [[Shirley & Company]] and released on the Vibration label. The lead singer is [[Shirley Goodman]], who was one half of Shirley and Lee, who had enjoyed a major hit 18 years earlier, in 1956, with the song \"[[Let the Good Times Roll (Shirley and Lee song)|Let The Good Times Roll]]\" for [[Aladdin Records]]. The male vocalist is [[Jason Alvarez|Jesus Alvarez]].<ref>Joel Whitburn's *Top Pop Singles, 12th Edition, 2009</ref> The saxophone solo is by [[Seldon Powell]], whose instrumental version, \"More Shame\", is the B-side.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://recordcollectormag.com/articles/maconblack|title=maconblack - Record Collector Magazine|website=recordcollectormag.com|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Shirley-Company-Shame-Shame-Shame/release/2501732|title=Shirley & Company - Shame, Shame, Shame|website=Discogs|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://curvetube.com/Seldon_Powell_And_Company-_More_Shame-_Parts_I_&_II/q9KN0beIPPA.video|title=Seldon Powell And Company- More Shame- Parts I & II|website=curvetube.com|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe track, with its prominent use of the [[Bo Diddley beat]], was one of the first international disco hits and reached number 12 on the [[Billboard charts]]. It also made number one on the [[soul music|soul]] singles chart for one week.<ref name=\"whitburn523\">{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=523}}</ref> The phrase \"got my sun roof down, got my diamonds in the back\" appeared as \"diamond in the back, sun roof top\" in [[William DeVaughn]]'s 1974 \"[[Be Thankful for What You Got]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1999/01/01/new-spin-on-a-golden-oldie/ef63a4c4-59d3-40f9-b990-0b44c474afcb/|title=NEW SPIN ON A GOLDEN OLDIE|first=Kevin|last=Merida|date=January 1, 1999|via=www.washingtonpost.com}}</ref>\n\n\"Shame, Shame, Shame\" also stayed at number one on the [[disco]]/dance charts for four weeks.<ref name=\"whitburn232\">{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=232}}</ref>  It was the sole success of this [[one-hit wonder]] band. a full-length album ''Shame, Shame, Shame'' was subsequently recorded and was released, howwver, in 1975.<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=shirley & company|bio=true}} Shirley & Company], Billboard</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n{{col-begin|width=65%}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (1974\u201375)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Australia [[Kent Music Report|KMR]]<ref name=\"austchartbook1970\">{{cite web|url=http://www.austchartbook.com.au/|title=Australian Chart Books|website=www.austchartbook.com.au|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Austria<ref>{{cite web|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://austriancharts.at/showitem.asp?interpret=Shirley+And+Company&titel=Shame%2C+Shame%2C+Shame&cat=s |title=Shirley And Company - Shame, Shame, Shame |website=Austriancharts.at |date= |accessdate=2016-10-10}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Belgium<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/song/15e/Shirley-And-Company-Shame,-Shame,-Shame |title=Shirley And Company - Shame, Shame, Shame |website=Ultratop.be |date= |accessdate=2016-10-10}}</ref> \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Canada ([[RPM (magazine)|''RPM'']])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.3938a&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.3938a.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.3938a |title=Image : RPM Weekly - Library and Archives Canada |website=Bac-lac.gc.ca |date= |accessdate=2016-10-10}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Germany<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicline.de/de/chartverfolgung_summary/title/Shirley+(%26+Company)/Shame,Shame,Shame/single |title=Die ganze Musik im Internet: Charts |website=Musicline.de |date= |accessdate=2016-10-10}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Netherlands]] ([[Dutch Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|author=Stichting Nederlandse Top 40 |url=http://www.top40.nl/top40/1975/week-12 |title=Top 40-lijst van week 12, 1975 |website=Top40.nl |date=1975-03-22 |accessdate=2016-10-10}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Recorded Music NZ|New Zealand]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=2635 |title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart &#124; The Official New Zealand Music Chart |website=Nztop40.co.nz |date=1975-05-12 |accessdate=2016-10-10}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Norway \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|9\n|-\n|South Africa ([[Springbok Radio]])<ref>{{cite web|title=SA Charts 1965\u2013March 1989|url=http://www.rock.co.za/files/springbok_top_20_(S).html|accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Switzerland \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|UK<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uk-charts.top-source.info/top-100-1975.shtml|title=Top 100 1975|author=|date=|work=top-source.info|accessdate=11 September 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"British Hit Singles & Albums\">{{cite book\n| first= David\n| last= Roberts\n| year= 2006\n| title= British Hit Singles & Albums\n| edition= 19th\n| publisher= Guinness World Records Limited \n| location= London\n| isbn= 1-904994-10-5\n| page= 496}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]]<ref>''Joel Whitburn's Top Pop Singles 1955-1990'' - {{ISBN|0-89820-089-X}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|12\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|US ''Billboard'' Disco/Dance<ref name=\"whitburn232\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|R&B]]<ref name=\"whitburn523\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|US [[Cashbox (magazine)|''Cash Box'']] Top 100<ref>{{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120930234604/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/_0s_files/196_0_XX.html |date=30 September 2012 |title=CASH BOX Top 100 Singles \u2013 Week ending MONTH DD, 19YY }}. [[Cashbox (magazine)|''Cash Box'' magazine]]. Retrieved 16 June 2016.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (1975)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Rank\n|-\n|Australia<ref name=\"austchartbook1970\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|82\n|-\n|Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.5173a&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=enic7sdhqrbeuu9iiip880d0j4|title=Item Display - RPM - Library and Archives Canada|work=collectionscanada.gc.ca}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|55\n|-\n|Germany<ref>[{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-1975| title=Top 100 Single-Jahrescharts| language=DE| publisher=offiziellecharts.de| accessdate=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|11\n|-\n|Netherlands <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/top-100-jaaroverzichten/1975|title=Top 100-Jaaroverzicht van 1975|first=Stichting Nederlandse|last=Top 40|website=Top40.nl}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|15\n|-\n|New Zealand<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/?chart=4046 |title=Top Selling Singles of 1975 &#124; The Official New Zealand Music Chart |website=Nztop40.co.nz |date=1975-12-31 |accessdate=2016-10-10}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|26\n|-\n|Switzerland <ref>{{cite web|url=http://swisscharts.com/charts/jahreshitparade/1975|title=Swiss Year-End Charts 1975 - swisscharts.com|first=Steffen|last=Hung|website=swisscharts.com|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|12\n|-\n|US ([[Joel Whitburn]]'s ''Pop Annual'')<ref>{{cite book |last=Whitburn |first=Joel |date=1999 |title=Pop Annual |url= |location=Menomonee Falls, Wisconsin |publisher=Record Research Inc. |page= |isbn=0-89820-142-X}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|122\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n==Cover versions==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Shame, Shame, Shame\n| cover      = SinittaShame.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Sinitta]]\n| album      = [[Naughty Naughty (album)|Naughty Naughty]]\n| B-side     = Maybe Someday\n| released   = 1992\n| format     = [[Gramophone record|7\" single]]\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[Soul music|soul]]\n| length     = 4:00\n| label      = [[Arista Records|Arista]]\n| writer     = [[Sylvia Robinson]]\n| producer   = [[Mark Taylor (music producer)|Mark Taylor]], Terry Adams\n| prev_title = [[Love and Affection]]\n| prev_year  = 1990\n| next_title = [[Aquarius (song)|Aquarius]]\n| next_year  = 1993\n}}\nLinda Fields & the Funky Boys recorded a version, sounding nearly identical and released it as a single in 1975; it was re-released in 1983 as a 12\" EP. The version appears on several disco compilation ablums and is often confused with the original. Their version charted concurrently with the original in New Zealand, reaching number 24.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.flavourofnz.co.nz/index.php?qpageID=search+rianz&qsongid=1941#n_view_location|title=flavour of new zealand - search rianz|website=www.flavourofnz.co.nz}}</ref> \n\nIn 1974 [[The Rolling Stones]] recorded the song, but it was never released. Also in 1974 [[Henri Salvador]] recorded a French version of the song, with the title \"J'aime tes g'noux\" (\"I like your [[knee]]s\").<ref> EP 7\" vinyl single [https://www.discogs.com/fr/Henri-Salvador-Jaime-Tes-Gnoux/release/3396407 ''J'aime tes g'noux''] (1974), by [[Henri Salvador]]. </ref>\n\n[[Tina Turner]] and [[Cher]] performed \"Shame, Shame, Shame\" on the [[Cher (TV series)|''Cher'' show]] in 1975. [[Ike & Tina Turner]]'s version was released on the 1980 album [[The Edge (Ike Turner album)|''The Edge'']]. The song was released as a single in Europe and peaked at number 47 in the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Ike+%26+Tina+Turner&titel=Shame%2C+Shame%2C+Shame&cat=s|title=Ike & Tina Turner - Shame, Shame, Shame|website=Dutch Charts}}</ref>\n\n[[Tina Charles (singer)|Tina Charles]] covered the song.{{cn}} Polish-Swedish singer [[Izabella Scorupco]] recorded a cover version of the song in 1992, with a video directed by [[Jonas \u00c5kerlund]].<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7225372/ Izabella: Shame, Shame, Shame (Video 1992) - IMDb<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It was a chart hit in a number of European countries and appears on an extended version of her 1991 album ''[[Iza (album)|Iza]]''. Also in 1992 the song was covered by British-American singer [[Sinitta]] and was released as a single, It peaked at number 28 in the [[UK Singles Chart]] and  was later included on her third studio album [[Naughty Naughty (album)|''Naughty Naughty'']] (1995).\n\nThe [[A-Teens]] recorded a cover of the song for their album ''[[New Arrival]]'' (2003).<ref>[https://www.laut.de/ATeens/Alben/New-Arrival-4437 \"New Arrival\" von A&ast;Teens \u2013 laut.de \u2013 Album<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n== Use in popular culture ==\n* In the 2014 film ''[[Pride (2014 film)|Pride]]'', Jonathan Blake ([[Dominic West]]) impresses the town of [[Onllwyn]] by [[disco dancing]] to the song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rogersmovienation.com/2014/10/08/dominic-west-and-the-real-jonathan-blake-talk-about-the-big-dance-in-pride/|title=Dominic West and the REAL Jonathan Blake talk about the big dance in \u201cPride\u201d|date=October 8, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of number-one hits of 1975 (Germany)]]\n*[[List of number-one dance singles of 1975 (U.S.)]]\n*[[List of number-one R&B singles of 1975 (U.S.)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}{{Ike & Tina Turner}}{{Sinitta}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shame, Shame, Shame (Shirley and Company song)}}\n[[Category:1974 singles]]\n[[Category:1992 singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Germany]]\n[[Category:Disco songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Sylvia Robinson]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Mark Taylor (record producer)]]\n[[Category:Philips Records singles]]\n[[Category:Arista Records singles]]\n[[Category:Ike & Tina Turner songs]]\n[[Category:Sinitta songs]]\n[[Category:Henri Salvador songs]]\n[[Category:A-Teens songs]]\n[[Category:1974 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Shame, Shame, Shame\n| cover      = SandC Shame.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Shirley & Company]]\n| album      = Shame, Shame, Shame\n| B-side     = {{ubl|\"More Shame\" (U.K., Europe)|\"Shame, Shame, Shame\" (Instrumental) (U.S.)}}\n| released   = December 1974\n| format     = [[CD single]], [[Gramophone record|7\" single]], [[Gramophone record|12\" single]]\n| recorded   = 1974\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Disco]], [[Soul music|soul]]\n| length     = 3:47\n| label      = Vibration\n| writer     = [[Sylvia Robinson]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Cry, Cry, Cry, (Shirley & Company song)|Cry, Cry, Cry]],\n| next_year  = 1975\n}}\n\n\"'''Shame, Shame, Shame'''\" is a 1974 hit song written by [[Sylvia Robinson]], performed by American [[disco]] band [[Shirley & Company]] and released on the Vibration label. The lead singer is [[Shirley Goodman]], who was one half of [[Shirley and Lee]], who had enjoyed a major hit 18 years earlier, in 1956, with the song \"[[Let the Good Times Roll (Shirley and Lee song)|Let The Good Times Roll]]\" for [[Aladdin Records]]. The male vocalist is [[Jason Alvarez|Jesus Alvarez]].<ref>Joel Whitburn's *Top Pop Singles, 12th Edition, 2009</ref> The saxophone solo is by [[Seldon Powell]], whose instrumental version, \"More Shame\", is the B-side.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://recordcollectormag.com/articles/maconblack|title=maconblack - Record Collector Magazine|website=recordcollectormag.com|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Shirley-Company-Shame-Shame-Shame/release/2501732|title=Shirley & Company - Shame, Shame, Shame|website=Discogs|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://curvetube.com/Seldon_Powell_And_Company-_More_Shame-_Parts_I_&_II/q9KN0beIPPA.video|title=Seldon Powell And Company- More Shame- Parts I & II|website=curvetube.com|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe track, with its prominent use of the [[Bo Diddley beat]], was one of the first international disco hits and reached number 12 on the [[Billboard charts]]. It also made number one on the [[soul music|soul]] singles chart for one week.<ref name=\"whitburn523\">{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=523}}</ref> The phrase \"got my sun roof down, got my diamonds in the back\" appeared as \"diamond in the back, sun roof top\" in [[William DeVaughn]]'s 1974 \"[[Be Thankful for What You Got]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1999/01/01/new-spin-on-a-golden-oldie/ef63a4c4-59d3-40f9-b990-0b44c474afcb/|title=NEW SPIN ON A GOLDEN OLDIE|first=Kevin|last=Merida|date=January 1, 1999|via=www.washingtonpost.com}}</ref>\n\n\"Shame, Shame, Shame\" also stayed at number one on the [[disco]]/dance charts for four weeks.<ref name=\"whitburn232\">{{cite book |title= Hot Dance/Disco: 1974-2003|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |authorlink=Joel Whitburn |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=232}}</ref>  It was the sole success of this [[one-hit wonder]] band. a full-length album ''Shame, Shame, Shame'' was subsequently recorded and was released, howwver, in 1975.<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=shirley & company|bio=true}} Shirley & Company], Billboard</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n{{col-begin|width=65%}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (1974\u201375)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Australia [[Kent Music Report|KMR]]<ref name=\"austchartbook1970\">{{cite web|url=http://www.austchartbook.com.au/|title=Australian Chart Books|website=www.austchartbook.com.au|accessdate=13 December 2017}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Austria<ref>{{cite web|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://austriancharts.at/showitem.asp?interpret=Shirley+And+Company&titel=Shame%2C+Shame%2C+Shame&cat=s |title=Shirley And Company - Shame, Shame, Shame |website=Austriancharts.at |date= |accessdate=2016-10-10}}</ref>\n| style=