{"title_page": "Carol A. Murphy", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| image           = Assemblywoman_Carol_Murphy.png\n| name            = Carol Murphy\n| office1         = Member of the [[New Jersey General Assembly]] from the [[7th Legislative District (New Jersey)|7th District]]\n| term_start1     = January 9, 2018\n| term_end1       =\n| alongside1      = [[Herb Conaway]]\n| predecessor1    = [[Troy Singleton]]\n| successor1      = \n| birth_date      = \n| birth_place     =\n| spouse          = \n| children        =\n| party           = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrat]]\n| alma_mater      = [[Camden County College]], Institute for Paralegal Studies, [[Kaplan University]]\n| residence       = [[Mount Laurel, New Jersey]]\n| website         = [http://www.njleg.state.nj.us/members/BIO.asp?Leg=397 Legislative Website]\n}}\n\n'''Carol A. Murphy''' is an American [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]] [[politician]], who has served in the [[New Jersey General Assembly]] since January 9, 2018. \n\n== New Jersey Assembly ==\nA resident of [[Mount Laurel, New Jersey|Mount Laurel]], she has represented the [[7th Legislative District (New Jersey)|7th Legislative District]] in the [[New Jersey]] [[New Jersey Assembly|Assembly]] since 2018, replacing [[Troy Singleton]], who relinquished his seat to successfully run for the [[New Jersey Senate]].<ref name=NJLEG>[http://www.njleg.state.nj.us/members/BIO.asp?Leg=401 Legislative web page], [[New Jersey Legislature]]. Accessed January 11, 2018.</ref> She was the first Assemblywoman to represent the 7th Legislative District in 20 years, with the last Assemblywoman for the district having been elected in 1995.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304203917/http://nj.gov/state/elections/election-results/1995-general-election-results-general-assembly.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=2016-03-04|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Committees<ref>{{Cite web|url=https